## NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Files: snake_case (auth_service.dart, user_profile.dart)
- Classes: PascalCase (AuthService, UserProfile)
- Variables/Methods: camelCase (getCurrentUser, isLoggedIn)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_BASE_URL)
- Database tables: snake_case (user_profiles, travel_plans)

## SUPABASE INTEGRATION RULES

### Database Schema
```sql
-- Users table (handled by Supabase Auth)
auth.users (id, email, created_at, etc.)

-- User profiles
user_profiles (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  username TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  full_name TEXT,
  bio TEXT,
  avatar_url TEXT,
  mood_preferences JSONB,
  travel_preferences JSONB,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Travel plans
travel_plans (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  location TEXT NOT NULL,
  mood_tag TEXT NOT NULL,
  weather_condition TEXT,
  plan_data JSONB NOT NULL,
  is_public BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Social posts
social_posts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  travel_plan_id UUID REFERENCES travel_plans(id),
  caption TEXT,
  image_urls TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  location TEXT,
  mood_tag TEXT,
  likes_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Friendships
friendships (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  requester_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  addressee_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  status friendship_status DEFAULT 'pending',
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  UNIQUE(requester_id, addressee_id)
);

-- Post likes
post_likes (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  post_id UUID REFERENCES social_posts(id),
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  UNIQUE(user_id, post_id)
);
```

### RLS (Row Level Security) Policies
- Always enable RLS on all tables
- Users can only read/write their own profiles
- Travel plans: users can read public plans and their own private plans
- Social posts: users can read all posts, but only modify their own
- Friendships: users can only see friendships they're part of

