## AUTHENTICATION RULES

### Auth Service Pattern (Riverpod)
```dart
// Auth state provider
final authStateProvider = StateNotifierProvider<AuthStateNotifier, User?>((ref) {
  final authService = ref.watch(authServiceProvider);
  return AuthStateNotifier(authService);
});

class AuthStateNotifier extends StateNotifier<User?> {
  final AuthService _authService;
  
  AuthStateNotifier(this._authService) : super(_authService.currentUser) {
    // Listen to auth state changes
    Supabase.instance.client.auth.onAuthStateChange.listen((event) {
      if (event.event == AuthChangeEvent.signedIn) {
        state = event.session?.user;
      } else if (event.event == AuthChangeEvent.signedOut) {
        state = null;
      }
    });
  }
  
  Future<void> signIn({
    required String email,
    required String password,
    required Function(String) onError,
    required Function() onSuccess,
  }) async {
    try {
      final response = await _authService.signIn(email: email, password: password);
      if (response.success) {
        state = response.user;
        onSuccess();
      } else {
        onError(response.message ?? 'Sign in failed');
      }
    } catch (e) {
      onError('An unexpected error occurred');
    }
  }
}
```

### Auth State Management
- Use Riverpod StateNotifierProvider for auth state
- Listen to auth state changes in StateNotifier
- Implement proper session management with SharedPreferences
- Handle token refresh automatically through Supabase
- Redirect to login when session expires using go_router guards
- Synchronize auth state between Supabase and local storage

### User Profile Management
- Create user profile after successful registration
- Sync user data with Supabase profiles table
- Handle profile image uploads to Supabase Storage
- Implement profile update functionality

## NAVIGATION RULES (go_router)

### Router Configuration
```dart
final router = GoRouter(
  routes: [
    GoRoute(
      path: '/',
      builder: (context, state) => const SplashScreen(),
    ),
    GoRoute(
      path: '/main',
      builder: (context, state) => const MainScreen(),
    ),
    GoRoute(
      path: '/auth',
      builder: (context, state) => const AuthScreen(),
    ),
  ],
  redirect: (context, state) {
    final user = Supabase.instance.client.auth.currentUser;
    if (user == null && state.location != '/auth') {
      return '/auth';
    }
    return null;
  },
);
```

### Navigation Patterns
- Use context.go() for navigation
- Use context.push() for modal navigation
- Use context.pop() to go back
- Implement proper route guards for authentication
- Use query parameters for state passing

## API INTEGRATION RULES

### HTTP Client Setup (Dio)
```dart
class ApiClient {
  static final Dio _dio = Dio();
  
  static void setupInterceptors() {
    _dio.interceptors.add(LogInterceptor());
    _dio.interceptors.add(InterceptorsWrapper(
      onRequest: (options, handler) {
        // Add auth token to headers
        final token = Supabase.instance.client.auth.currentSession?.accessToken;
        if (token != null) {
          options.headers['Authorization'] = 'Bearer $token';
        }
        handler.next(options);
      },
      onError: (error, handler) {
        // Handle global errors
        if (error.response?.statusCode == 401) {
          // Handle unauthorized
        }
        handler.next(error);
      },
    ));
  }
}
```

### Error Handling Pattern
```dart
// Use AsyncValue for error handling with Riverpod
final chatStateProvider = StateNotifierProvider<ChatNotifier, AsyncValue<List<ChatMessage>>>((ref) {
  return ChatNotifier();
});

class ChatNotifier extends StateNotifier<AsyncValue<List<ChatMessage>>> {
  ChatNotifier() : super(const AsyncValue.loading()) {
    _loadMessages();
  }

  Future<void> _loadMessages() async {
    try {
      state = const AsyncValue.loading();
      final messages = await ChatService.getChatMessages();
      state = AsyncValue.data(messages);
    } catch (error, stackTrace) {
      state = AsyncValue.error(error, stackTrace);
    }
  }
}

// In UI - handle AsyncValue states
ref.watch(chatStateProvider).when(
  data: (messages) => MessagesList(messages: messages),
  loading: () => const CircularProgressIndicator(),
  error: (error, stack) => ErrorWidget(error: error),
);
```

## OPENAI INTEGRATION RULES

### AI Service for Travel Recommendations
```dart
class AIService {
  final String _apiKey = AppConfig.openaiApiKey;
  final Dio _dio = Dio();

  Future<TravelRecommendation> generateTravelPlan({
    required String location,
    required String mood,
    required String weather,
    required Map<String, dynamic> preferences,
  }) async {
    final prompt = _buildPrompt(location, mood, weather, preferences);
    
    try {
      final response = await _dio.post(
        'https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions',
        options: Options(
          headers: {
            'Authorization': 'Bearer $_apiKey',
            'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          },
        ),
        data: {
          'model': 'gpt-4',
          'messages': [
            {'role': 'system', 'content': 'You are a travel planning assistant...'},
            {'role': 'user', 'content': prompt},
          ],
          'max_tokens': 1000,
          'temperature': 0.7,
        },
      );
      
      return _parseResponse(response.data);
    } catch (e) {
      throw AIServiceException('Failed to generate travel plan: $e');
    }
  }
}
```

### AI Prompt Engineering
- Create detailed system prompts for travel planning
- Include mood-to-activity mapping
- Consider weather conditions in recommendations
- Include user preferences and constraints
- Format responses as structured JSON

### AI Response Caching
- Cache AI responses in local storage
- Implement cache expiration (24 hours)
- Use location + mood + weather as cache key
- Reduce API costs with intelligent caching

