## STATE MANAGEMENT RULES (Riverpod)

### Riverpod Structure
```dart
// Main app with ProviderScope
runApp(
  ProviderScope(
    overrides: [
      sharedPreferencesProvider.overrideWithValue(prefs),
    ],
    child: const WanderMoodApp(),
  ),
);
```

### Provider Patterns
- Use StateNotifierProvider for complex state management
- Use FutureProvider for async data fetching
- Use StreamProvider for real-time data streams
- Use StateProvider for simple state
- Implement proper error handling with AsyncValue

### State Class Patterns with Freezed
```dart
@freezed
class MoodState with _$MoodState {
  const factory MoodState.initial() = _Initial;
  const factory MoodState.loading() = _Loading;
  const factory MoodState.loaded({
    required List<Mood> moods,
    @Default([]) List<Activity> activities,
  }) = _Loaded;
  const factory MoodState.error(String message) = _Error;
}
```

### StateNotifier Pattern
```dart
class MoodNotifier extends StateNotifier<MoodState> {
  late final MoodService _service;

  MoodNotifier(this._service) : super(const MoodState.initial());

  Future<void> getMoods() async {
    state = const MoodState.loading();
    try {
      final moods = await _service.getMoods();
      state = MoodState.loaded(moods: moods);
    } catch (e) {
      state = MoodState.error(e.toString());
    }
  }
}

// Provider definition
final moodProvider = StateNotifierProvider<MoodNotifier, MoodState>((ref) {
  return MoodNotifier(ref.watch(moodServiceProvider));
});
```

### Consumer Usage
```dart
// In widgets, use Consumer or ref.watch
Consumer(
  builder: (context, ref, child) {
    final moodState = ref.watch(moodProvider);
    return moodState.when(
      initial: () => const InitialWidget(),
      loading: () => const LoadingWidget(),
      loaded: (moods, activities) => LoadedWidget(moods: moods),
      error: (message) => ErrorWidget(message: message),
    );
  },
)
```

